                                "byte_start": 105472,
                                "byte_stop": 126161,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas has the opinion of the Court in two cases this morning."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 5.157,
                        "stop": 246.988,
                        "byte_start": 126161,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15100,
                            "name": "Clarence Thomas",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/clarence_thomas",
                            "last_name": "Thomas",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2744,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 688194000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2744"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32680,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49064,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/clarence_thomas.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8870,
                            "identifier": "clarence_thomas"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 5.157,
                                "stop": 20.972,
                                "byte_start": 126161,
                                "byte_stop": 189377,
                                "text": "First case in which I have the opinion is 08-1214, Granite Rock Company versus the International Brotherhood of Teamsters."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 20.972,
                                "stop": 29.177,
                                "byte_start": 189377,
                                "byte_stop": 222187,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on the writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 29.177,
                                "stop": 43.625,
                                "byte_start": 222187,
                                "byte_stop": 280074,
                                "text": "Petitioner Granite Rock is a California Company that that employs members of the respondent unions, Teamsters local and its parent respondent International Brotherhood of Teamster."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 43.625,
                                "stop": 49.394,
                                "byte_start": 280074,
                                "byte_stop": 303062,
                                "text": "I will refer to former as local and the later as IBT."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 49.394,
                                "stop": 63.318,
                                "byte_start": 303062,
                                "byte_stop": 358755,
                                "text": "Granite Rock\u2019s relationship with local is governed by a collective bargaining agreement or CBA that Granite Rock negotiated with local on July 2nd, 2004."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 63.318,
                                "stop": 76.891,
                                "byte_start": 358755,
                                "byte_stop": 413090,
                                "text": "This case arose out of a strike that local initiated, Granite Rock sued the Union and in District Court claiming that strike violated the CBAs No Strike clause."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 76.891,
                                "stop": 82.027,
                                "byte_start": 413090,
                                "byte_stop": 433674,
                                "text": "Granite Rock also sued IBT for interfering with the CBA."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 82.027,
                                "stop": 86.523,
                                "byte_start": 433674,
                                "byte_stop": 451647,
                                "text": "Local and IBT moved to dismiss Granite Rock suit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 86.523,
                                "stop": 99.578,
                                "byte_start": 451647,
                                "byte_stop": 503787,
                                "text": "The District Court granted IBT\u2019s motion to dismiss finding that a Federal Court can not recognize a tort claim for interference with the CBA by a non-signatory."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 99.578,
                                "stop": 115.856,
                                "byte_start": 503787,
                                "byte_stop": 568989,
                                "text": "Local in turn argued that its strike did not violate the CBA\u2019s No Strike Provision because its members had not yet voted to ratify the CBA and thus the CBA was not yet enforceable."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 115.856,
                                "stop": 132.375,
                                "byte_start": 568989,
                                "byte_stop": 635026,
                                "text": "Local also argued that Granite Rock\u2019s No Strike claim did not belong in Federal Court because the CBA required all disputes arising under its provision to go to arbitration."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 132.375,
                                "stop": 153.181,
                                "byte_start": 635026,
                                "byte_stop": 718200,
                                "text": "The District Court agreed with local that Granite Rock\u2019s No Strike claim was arbitratable but held that there was a factual question about when the CBA was ratified and this question was before that Court not an Arbitrator to resolve."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 153.181,
                                "stop": 162.716,
                                "byte_start": 718200,
                                "byte_stop": 756339,
                                "text": "After Jury found that the CBA was ratified on July 2nd, the court sent Granite Rocks No-Strike claim to arbitration."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 162.716,
                                "stop": 164.872,
                                "byte_start": 756339,
                                "byte_stop": 765012,
                                "text": "All parties appealed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 164.872,
                                "stop": 175.411,
                                "byte_start": 765012,
                                "byte_stop": 807121,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals affirmed the District Court\u0027s dismissal of Granite Rocks claims against IBT but reversed the District Court\u0027s arbitration rule."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 175.411,
                                "stop": 180.724,
                                "byte_start": 807121,
                                "byte_stop": 828437,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the Clerk, we reversed in part, affirm in part."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 180.724,
                                "stop": 201.391,
                                "byte_start": 828437,
                                "byte_stop": 911088,
                                "text": "We reversed the Court of Appeal\u2019s arbitration ruling because it does not accord with our decisions that arbitration is strictly a matter of agreement, thus a Court may not order parties to arbitrate the particular dispute unless the court is satisfied that the parties agreed to arbitrate that dispute."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 201.391,
                                "stop": 208.149,
                                "byte_start": 911088,
                                "byte_stop": 938151,
                                "text": "The record and arguments probably before us do not establish that Granite Rock agreed to do so."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 208.149,
                                "stop": 238.771,
                                "byte_start": 938151,
                                "byte_stop": 1060613,
                                "text": "We affirm the District Court, the Court of Appeals refusal to recognize new Federal tort claim under the Labor Management Relations Act, that Granite Rock alleges against IBT even assuming that the Act authorizes us to recognize the claim, the record does not support Granite Rock\u2019s argument that such a claim would be necessary to supplement other means of addressing IBT\u2019s alleged interference with the CBA."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 238.771,
                                "stop": 246.988,
                                "byte_start": 1060613,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Sotomayor has filed an opinion concurring in part and dissenting in part, in which Justice Stevens joins."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
